All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Board
Represents a 6x6 Sudoku board and provides functionality to initialize and manage the board.
BoardAdapter
The abstract class BoardAdapter provides a default implementation of the IBoard interface.
GameBoard
The GameBoard class represents a 6x6 Sudoku-like game board.
GameController
The GameController class handles user interactions in the game stage of the game.
GameStage
Represents the game stage of the Sudoku game.
IBoard
The IBoard interface defines the essential methods and default implementations for handling the Sudoku game board, including validation of numbers by column, row, and box, as well as setting numbers and displaying the board.
IInput
The IInput interface defines the methods for validating user input in the Sudoku game.
Input
The Input class provides methods to handle and validate user input for the Sudoku game.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point of the Sudoku application.
WelcomeController
The WelcomeController class handles the user interactions on the welcome screen of the Sudoku game.
WelcomeStage
Represents the welcome stage of the Sudoku game.
